				<li id="16477814" class="cmnt-root" data="5" data-d="1646792634000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t578560/Loretta's-Greatbow" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">08 Mar 2022 21:23</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16477814" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">I use this spell all the time. It&apos;s fun and cool, has fantastic range, decent tracking, and high damage for PVE. It&apos;s also exceptional for PVP because not only is it the only spell I know of that you can hold indefinitely (except I assume the quadruple version), but you can cancel it without spending FP by rolling once it&apos;s max charge. This means you can put pressure on an invader and force them on the defensive because if they try and attack someone you let it fly and catch them mid animation. If they retreat out of LOS you just cancel it. The explosion can even roll catch sometimes. Usually most invaders leave once they realize that this is happening because honestly there isn&apos;t a whole lot they can do if it&apos;s a large space.</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16477814" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16477814" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies (<span class="replies">0</span>)</a><div class