				<li id="16443676" class="cmnt-root" data="1" data-d="1646369394000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><a class="comment-username" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&u=125164" rel="nofollow"  target="_blank" style="color: #;">flannoit</a></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t578560/Loretta's-Greatbow" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">03 Mar 2022 23:49</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16443676" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">The cast time is a bit excessively long, and you CANNOT move for the final stage of cast or at all during the actual firing. The damage doesn&apos;t seem to really outweigh the cast time, but it does seem to very reliably trigger stance/guard breaking, but not for critical hits. Not sure what the range on it is in comparison to Glintstone Pebble, though it is definitely deals more damage than it. It&apos;ll definitely have its use on enemies who turtle or possibly for long-range shots if it outranges Glintstone Pebble like Magic Glintblade does.</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16443676" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16443676" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies (<span class="replies">3</span>)</a><div class="vote pull-right"><section class="t-up"><span></span><p>1</p><i class="add">+1</i></se